Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BoardInterface
    BoardInterface represents the board state in the game of tabula (not including dice and players).
    DiceInterface
    DiceInterface represents a pair of dice as used in tabula.
    DieInterface
    DieInterface represents a single die.
    GameInterface
    GameInterface represent the game state including the board, the dice and the players Requires a constructor with no parameters.
    LocationInterface
    LocationInterface represents a single location on the board, but not its position Locations on the main part of the board may only contain a single colour of piece.
    MoveInterface
    MoveInterface represents the use of a single Die to move a single piece.
    PlayerInterface
    PlayerInterface represents a player in the game of tabula Up to three different implementations of this interface can be provided: HumanConsolePlayer; ; ComputerPlayer; HumanGUIPlayer Each implementation requires a constructor with no parameters.
    TurnInterface
    TurnInterface represents a series of moves which constitute a turn by a player.
